Module simplifier
Package ie.gmit.dip

Interface Optionable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    RunnableCommandLineOption
    public interface Optionable
    Optionable is an abstract interface which declares the functional behavior expected of an option which a user may wish to select or run. Behavior is largely that associated with a Bean class, with the only requirements being methods to define the option number, the option text, and any help text associated with the option.
    Since:
    JavaSE-11
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Kieran P. Somers
    See Also:
